result.execSummary:
This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Leobardo Dominguez-Aparicio in court with attorney Colin Patrick McGinn.  Erika Strebel appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Student Intern Caroline Pelligrini supervised by Erika Strebel appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  

Case in court for Scheduling Conference. Defense request a plea date. 
Defense  advised to the plea documents 24 hours in advance of the hearing,. 
Court ordered matter adjourned back to Branch 19.  Plea hearing scheduled for November 16, 2022 at 10:30 am.

Defendant Leobardo Dominguez-Aparicio in court with attorney Colin Patrick McGinn, appear by video.  Abby Rockendorf appeared in person for the State of Wisconsin.  
Preliminary hearing proceeded. Sworn as interpreter: Kelley D. Salas. Sworn for the State: MPD Officer J. Jenson. State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty.  Case is adjourned to Branch 45.  Pursuant to Chief Judge Directive 22-04, parties are hereby notified that as of July 30, 2022, this case will be assigned to Branch 6, Judge Ellen Brostrom, in Room 608 of the Courthouse.  Scheduling conference scheduled for August 17, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Public Defender Order Appointing Counsel, Filed.
Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with RFP

Court ordered Justice Point Pretrial Services LEVEL 1 SUPERVISION.  Court reminders.
Defendant advised it is a requirement to attend all future court proceedings.
Failure to comply with conditions of bail may result in an additional charge of bail jumping.

Defendant Leobardo Dominguez-Aparicio in court with attorney Edgar A Beltran.  Defendant Leobardo Dominguez-Aparicio in custody.  Samuel E. Simpson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy court clerk cmt.
Hearing held via Zoom.  Sworn as interpreter: leisl Monroy. Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Kies, Branch 45. Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for June 2, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
